<li class="sdc-article-related-stories__item"><a class="sdc-article-related-stories__link" href="http://www.skysports.com/bundesliga-results">Bundesliga results</a></li>
<li class="sdc-article-related-stories__item"><a class="sdc-article-related-stories__link" href="http://www.skysports.com/bundesliga-table">Bundesliga table</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li><strong><a href="https://www.skysports.com/bundesliga">Bundesliga news</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://www.skysports.com/bundesliga-fixtures">Fixtures</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://www.skysports.com/bundesliga-table">Table</a></strong></li>
</ul>
<p>But they were nowhere to be seen in the first half with Kramaric ramming the ball in for the lead in the 19th minute after a good move by Robert Skov and Ilhas Bebou, cleverly letting the ball slide through his legs for his teammate to score.</p>
<div class="sdc-article-widget sdc-article-image">
<figure class="sdc-article-image__figure">
<div class="sdc-article-image__wrapper" data-aspect-ratio="16/9"><img class="sdc-article-image__item" src="https://e0.365dm.com/21/10/768x432/skysports-hoffenheim-bundesliga_5564299.jpg?20211029213740" sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw" srcset="https://e0.365dm.com/21/10/384x216/skysports-hoffenheim-bundesliga_5564299.jpg?20211029213740 380w, https://e0.365dm.com/21/10/768x432/skysports-hoffenheim-bundesliga_5564299.jpg?20211029213740 760w, https://e0.365dm.com/21/10/1600x900/skysports-hoffenheim-bundesliga_5564299.jpg?20211029213740 1024w, https://e0.365dm.com/21/10/2048x1152/skysports-hoffenheim-bundesliga_5564299.jpg?20211029213740 2048w" alt="Hoffenheim were 2-0 winners on Friday evening" /></div>
<figcaption class="sdc-article-image__caption"><span class="sdc-article-image__visually-hidden">Image:</span><span class="sdc-article-image__caption-text">Hoffenheim were 2-0 winners on Friday evening</span></figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
<p>The Croat has now scored nine goals in 11 matches against Hertha, more than against any other Bundesliga club.</p>
<p>The hosts, who have now won seven of their last nine games at home in all competitions, kept their foot on the gas and Skov rattled the post with a thundering shot in the 36th minute, only for the rebound to land conveniently into the path of Rudy who connected perfectly to double their lead.</p>
<p>To make matters worse, Hertha were left with 10 men when captain Dedryck Boyata was sent off with a straight red card for a late and extremely dangerous challenge on Angelo Stiller, who had to be taken off with an ankle injury.</p>
<p>Hertha coach Pal Dardai continues his bad run at Hoffenheim in his 200th game in charge of the Berlin club, and has now managed just one point in his seven visits, with his team dropping to 11th place on 12 points. Hoffenheim move up to seventh on 14 points.</p>
